parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor stops working
the seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt is locked in place
the seat belt comes out of the buckle during an accident
the seat belt does not keep the driver from hitting the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt comes out of the buckle during an accident
the seat belt buckle fails to release
the seat belt buckle is jammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate design of the seat belt can cause difficulties in fastening, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The driver's shoulder belt is too short
causing fastening difficulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents. Additionally, it can also lead to further damage to other brake components, such as rotors and calipers.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
vibrations when braking
uneven brake pad wear
excessive dust or debris from the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake rotor failure can cause vibrations when braking, reduced stopping power, and potentially lead to accidents. It can also cause further damage to other brake components, such as brake pads and calipers.
symptoms: Vibrations when braking
squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
uneven brake rotor wear
excessive heat buildup around the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective brake calipers can cause uneven brake pad wear, reduced stopping power, and potentially lead to accidents. It can also cause further damage to other brake components, such as brake rotors and pads.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
vibrations when braking
uneven brake pad wear
excessive heat buildup around the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the front coil springs can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and may also result in damage to other suspension components.
symptoms: The front coil springs break or fracture
often without warning
while driving or stationary
causing a sudden loss of ride height
noise
and potential loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A misaligned front end can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and affect overall vehicle safety.
symptoms: Noise from the front end
uneven tire wear
and potentially
vibrations while driving.
